#: ../../N/nethack.rst:5
msgid "nethack"
msgstr "nethack"

#: ../../N/nethack.rst:7
msgid "/net´hak/, n\\."
msgstr "/net´hak/, 名詞"

#: ../../N/nethack.rst:9
msgid ""
"[Unix] A dungeon game similar to :ref:`rogue` but more elaborate, "
"distributed in C source over :ref:`Usenet` and very popular at Unix sites "
"and on PC-class machines (nethack is probably the most widely distributed of"
" the freeware dungeon games). The earliest versions, written by Jay Fenlason"
" and later considerably enhanced by Andries Brouwer, were simply called "
"‘hack’. The name changed when maintenance was taken over by a group of "
"hackers originally organized by Mike Stephenson. There is now an official "
"site at `http://www.nethack.org/ <http://www.nethack.org/>`_. See also "
":ref:`moria`\\, :ref:`rogue`\\, :ref:`Angband`\\."
msgstr ""
"[Unix] \\ :ref:`rogue`\\ に似ているがより精巧なダンジョンゲーム。Cソースで\\ :ref:`Usenet`\\ "
"上に配布され、UnixサイトやクラスPCの機械で非常に人気がある(nethackはおそらくフリーウェアのダンジョンゲームの中で最も広く配布されている)。Jay"
" Fenlasonによって書かれ、後にAndries "
"Brouwerによってかなり強化された最初期のバージョンは、単に‘hack’と呼ばれていた。保守をMike "
"Stephensonが当初組織したハッカーのグループが引き継いだとき、名前が変わった。今では\\ `http://www.nethack.org/ "
"<http://www.nethack.org/>`_\\ に公式サイトがある。\\ :ref:`moria`\\ 、\\ :ref:`rogue`\\"
" 、\\ :ref:`Angband`\\ も参照。"
